Pre-caudal vertebrae 14 , caudal vertebrae 21 . Ventral profile of supraorbital curved, its articular surface with lateral ethmoid almost straight (
Fig. 3 - 1
); third suborbital slender, its dorsal profile concave, its posterior end much broader than anterior end (
Fig. 3 - 2
); maxilla slender, slightly curved, its ventral margin straight (
Fig. 3 - 3
); dentary with coronoid process blunt, its inferior border slightly convex, its superior border with a prominent depression (
Fig. 3-4
); fifth ceratobranchial curved, its posterior margin smooth, with 5 + 4 + 2 distally curved teeth (
Fig. 3-5
); postero-dorsal margin of opercle slightly concave, its postero-ventral margin straight (
Fig. 3-6
); caudal skeleton with first neural spine simple, sixth hypural greatly reduced, its length less than half of fifth (
Fig. 3-7
).

